Key Match Events: Joel Embiid had 28 points and 12 rebounds, leading the Philadelphia 76ers to a 123-94 victory over the Brooklyn Nets.
Tyrese Maxey added 18 points, while Paul George and Caleb Martin each contributed 17 points for the 76ers.
Ziaire Williams scored 19 points and Keon Johnson added 15 points for the short-handed Nets.
Brooklyn was missing starters Cam Thomas, Cam Johnson, and Ben Simmons due to injuries.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Philadelphia fell behind 11-0 early in the game but responded with a 29-8 run to close out the first quarter.
The 76ers shot 57% in the second quarter to take a 64-47 lead at halftime.
Joel Embiid hit all 10 of his free throws.
The game was held at Barclays Center with an attendance of 17,926.
